"```sql\nSELECT a.account_id\nFROM client c\nJOIN disp d ON c.client_id = d.client_id\nJOIN account a ON d.account_id = a.account_id\nJOIN district di ON c.district_id = di.district_id\nWHERE c.gender = 'F'\nAND c.birth_date = (\n    SELECT MIN(birth_date)\n    FROM client\n    WHERE gender = 'F'\n)\nAND di.average_salary = (\n    SELECT MIN(average_salary)\n    FROM district\n)\n```\nThis SQL query selects the account numbers of female clients who are the oldest and have the lowest average salary. It uses joins to connect the relevant tables based on the foreign key relationships and applies the necessary conditions to filter the results."